\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{x}_{i}=\frac{1}{|D_{i}|}\sum_{j\in D_{i}}f_{\mathrm{Sentence\ embed}}(C^{(j)})
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $D_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the set of vectors where each vector represents a sentence in the i-th
 document, 
\begin_inset Formula $|D_{i}|$
\end_inset

 is a cardinality of 
\begin_inset Formula $D_{i}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $C^{(j)}$
\end_inset

 is a matrix of ùëó-th sentence where words are encoded with one hot or byte
 pair encoding [20] 
